  "title": "Executive Secretary",
  "description": "<h3><strong>Executive Secretary (Confidential Search)</strong></h3>\n<p>We are partnering with a leading private organization to hire an <strong>Executive Secretary</strong> who will act as the <strong>strategic and operational right hand</strong> to a senior business leader. This role goes beyond administrative duties — it requires strong business judgment, foresight, and the ability to operate as a trusted executive partner in a dynamic environment.</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p><strong>Key Responsibilities:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Provide high-level strategic and administrative support to the senior leader.</li>\n  <li>Manage complex scheduling, travel, and stakeholder communications.</li>\n  <li>Draft and handle confidential correspondence and reports with professionalism.</li>\n  <li>Coordinate cross-functional projects and ensure timely follow-through.</li>\n  <li>Oversee selected personal or lifestyle matters discreetly to support business focus.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Requirements:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Diploma/Degree in Business or related field.</li>\n  <li>3 to 5 years of experience supporting C-suite or business owners.</li>\n  <li>Excellent communication skills in English and Mandarin to liaise with Mandarin-speaking colleagues and counterparts</li>\n  <li>Resourceful, proactive, and able to work independently in fast-paced settings.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>You are not just an assistant — you are a strategic partner</strong> who anticipates needs, ensures seamless execution, and amplifies leadership effectiveness.</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p>We appreciate your interest and look forward to reviewing your application. Due to high application volume, only shortlisted candidates will be contacted — thank you for your understanding!</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p>WeCruit Pte Ltd | EA License No. 20C0270</p>\n<p>EA Personnel: Tan Soon Hock (Steven) | Registration No. R1109889</p>",
